    "To compute w ⋆ we would not compute the inverse, but rather solve two sets of equations to find Σ -1 µ and Σ -1 1 [BV18].",
    "Still, the appearance of Σ -1 in the expressions for the solutions give us a hint that the method can be sensitive to the input data when the covariance matrix Σ is nearly singular.",
    "These analytical formulas can also be used to back out so-called implied returns, i.e., the mean µ for which a given portfolio is optimal.",
